hey were outcasts who live in the underground tunnels beneath New York, New Jersey, and Connecticut known as the [[Morlocks (comics)|Morlocks]].{{Issue|date=August 2011}}\\n\\nPlague was present during the Morlock [[Mutant Massacre|massacre]] by the [[Marauders (comics)|Marauders]] and was terrorized by [[Sabretooth (comics)|Sabretooth]], who was unaware of her abilities and left weakened and might have died if not for his healing factor.{{Issue|date=August 2011}} [[Apocalypse (comics)|Apocalypse]] arrived and saved Plague from the massacre, stating that he had plans for her to serve him as the Horseman Pestilence.<ref name=\\"X-Factor_10\\">\'\'X-Factor\'\' #10</ref>\\n\\nAfter being transformed into Pestilence, Plague, [[War (Marvel Comics character)|War]], and [[Famine (comics)|Famine]] battled [[X-Factor (comics)|X-Factor]] in Central Park and were defeated by [[Iceman (comics)|Iceman]], but not before they killed countless humans.<ref name=\\"X-Factor_10\\" /> After the fourth Horseman, [[Warren Worthington|Death]], was revealed, Apocalypse had the Horsemen battle each other, to find the leader and Death beat them all.{{Issue|date=August 2011}}\\n\\nAfter Apocalypse teleported X-Factor on his Celestial Ship, they battled the Horsemen again and, after their defeat, the Horsemen were sent into Manhattan to incite chaos.{{Issue|date=August 2011}} X-Factor and the Power Pack battled the Horsemen and Lightspeed knocked Pestilence off her flying steed, whereupon she fell to her death.<ref>\'\'Power Pack\'\' #35</ref>\\n\\n==Powers and abilities==\\nPlague\'s immune system made her essentially immune to all known diseases. However, she could be exposed to a disease, alter it to be more lethal, and then spread it by touch. Her power was augmented by Apocalypse to an unknown degree.{{Issue|date=January 2012}}\\n\\nAs Pestilence, she also utilized an electric flying robotic steed constructed by Apocalypse\'s Ship.{{Issue|date=January 2012}}\\n\\n==In other media==\\n===Television===\\n* Plague first makes a cameo in the \'\'[[X-Men (TV series)|X-Men]]\'\' episode \\"Captive Hearts\\", voiced by [[Judy Marshak]]. She appears as one of the Morlocks fighting the X-Men and incapacitating Gambit. She returns in the episode \\"[[Come the Apocalypse]]\\" wanting a cure and is eventually transformed into the Horseman Pestilence.\\n\\n==References==\\n{{reflist}}\\n\\n[[Category:Characters created by Chris Claremont]]\\n[[Category:Comics characters introduced in 1983]]\\n[[Category:Fictional henchmen]]\\n[[Category:Marvel Comics mutants]]\\n[[Category:Marvel Comics supervillains]]\\n\\n{{Marvel-villain-stub}}"}]}}}}'